#: APP-MANAGER:2304
msgid   "DESCRIPTION: A command line utility to install and manage AppImages and other portable programs for GNU/Linux thanks to its AUR-inspired database."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2305
msgid   "OPTION"
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2306
msgid   "OPTIONS"
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2307
msgid   "THIRD-PARTY FLAGS"
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2308
msgid   "Third-party databases"
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2309
msgid   "SITES"
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2312
msgid   "Description: Shows more info about one or more apps."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2313
msgid   "Description: Accede to github APIs using your personal access tokens. The file named \\\"ghapikey.txt\\\" will be saved in $AMDATADIR. Use \\\"del\\\" to remove it."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2314
msgid   "Description: Create a snapshot of the current version of an installed program."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2315
msgid   "Description: Removes all the unnecessary files and folders."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2316
msgid   "Description: Clone the list of installed apps to an \\\"am-clone.source\\\" file, or search for an existing one on the desktop (priority), in $HOME, or across the entire system and removable devices. Add \\\"-i\\\" or \\\"install\\\" if you want to install or add the listed apps to a new configuration, to share it with anyone on other PCs and configurations. Add the \\\"--system\\\" or \\\"--user\\\" flag if you want all listed apps to be installed system-wide or locally respectively.\n"
        "\n"
        "\t\t\tYou can also set the path to a custom file by exporting the \\$CLONE_FILE variable."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2319
msgid   "Description: Set a dedicated \\$XDG_CONFIG_HOME for one or more AppImages."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2320
msgid   "Description: Download an older or specific app version."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2321
msgid   "Description: Download one or more installation scripts to your desktop or convert them to local installers for \\\"AppMan\\\". To test the scripts, use the \\\"$AMCLI -i '/path/to/script'\\\" command or enter the directory of the script and run the \\\"$AMCLI -i ./script\\\" command, even using dedicated flags, if necessary (see \\\"-i\\\")."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2322
msgid   "Description: Install AppImages from github.com, outside the database. This allows you to install, update and manage them all like the others. Where \\\"user/project\\\" can be the whole URL to the github repository, give a name to the program so that it can be used from the command line. Optionally, add an \\\"univoque\\\" keyword if multiple AppImages are listed."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2323
msgid   "Description: Shows the list of all installed programs, with sizes. By default apps are sorted by size, use \\\"--byname\\\" to sort by name. With the option \\\"--less\\\" it shows only the number of installed apps. Option \\\"-fi\\\" only shows installed apps, not the AppImages integrated with the \\\"--launcher\\\" option."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2324
msgid   "Description: Prints this message."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2325
msgid   "Description: Prevents an installed application from being shown or managed by \\\"$AMCLI\\\"."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2326
msgid   "Description: Set a dedicated \\$HOME directory for one or more AppImages."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2327
msgid   "Description: Set dedicated \\$HOME and \\$XDG_CONFIG_HOME directories for one or more AppImages."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2328
msgid   "Description: Allow installed apps to use system icon themes. You can specify the name of the apps to change or use the \\\"--all\\\" flag to change all of them at once. This will remove the icon path from the .desktop file and add the symbolic link of all available icons in the $DATADIR/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps directory. The \\\"--icons\\\" option can be used as \\\"flag\\\" in the \\\"-i\\\" and \\\"-ia\\\" options."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2329
msgid   "Description: Install one or more programs or libraries from the list. With the \\\"--debug\\\" option you can see log messages to debug the script. For more details on \\\"--force-latest\\\", see the dedicated option, below. Use the \\\"--icons\\\" flag to allow the program to use icon themes. The \\\"--sandbox\\\" flag allows you to set sandboxes for AppImage packages. It can also be extended with additional flags (see third-party flags, at the bottom of this message)."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2330
msgid   "Description: Same as \\\"install\\\" (see above) but for AppImages only. Option \\\"-ias\\\" (aka Install AppImage & Sandbox) is equivalent to \\\"-ia --sandbox\\\", to set sandboxes for AppImage packages."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2331
msgid   "Description: Shows the list of all the apps available. Without flags only shows the apps in the \\\"AM\\\" database, add the \\\"--appimages\\\" to show only the AppImages or \\\"--portable\\\" to show other formats from the \\\"AM\\\" database. The \\\"--all\\\" flag allows you to consult the set of all supported third-party databases. It can also be extended with additional flags (see third-party flags, at the bottom of this message)."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2332
msgid   "Description: Prevent an application being updated, if it has an\\\"AM-updater\\\" script."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2333
msgid   "Description: Set a new default repo, use \\\"add\\\" to append the path to a local directory or an online URL, then use \\\"select\\\" to use it by default, a message will warn you about the usage of this repo instead of the default one. Use \\\"on\\\"/\\\"off\\\" to enable/disable it. Use \\\"purge\\\" to remove all 3rd party repos. Use \\\"info\\\" to see the source from where installation scripts and lists are taken."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2334
msgid   "Description: Convert old AppImages and get rid of \\\"libfuse2\\\" dependence."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2335
msgid   "Description: Overwrite apps with snapshots saved previously (see \\\"-b\\\")."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2336
msgid   "Description: Search for keywords in the list of available applications, add the \\\"--appimages\\\" option to list only the AppImages, \\\"--portable\\\" option to list only the portable apps or add \\\"--pkg\\\" to list multiple programs at once. The \\\"--all\\\" flag allows you to consult the set of all supported databases."
msgstr  ""

#: APP-MANAGER:2337
